If your case is not very performance-sensitive and not streaming, you can do something like this:

```
var bomUsed = false;
var res = iconv.decode(buf, "utf8", {stripBOM: function() { bomUsed = true });
if (!bomUsed)
  res = iconv.decode(buf, "1255");
```

stripBOM parameter acts both as flag and as a callback that is called when BOM exists.

If streaming is required, then you can write small wrapper that would do the detection, similar to [StripBOMWrapper](https://github.com/ashtuchkin/iconv-lite/blob/master/lib/bom-handling.js#L28).

